James de Villiers, News 24 (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Western Cape Social Development MEC Albert Fritz warned social grant recipients on Tuesday of a scam involving people being asked to divulge their pin numbers in exchange for a Christmas hamper. Fritz said he received a tip-off about a scam involving a person claiming to be from the SA Social Security Agency&nbsp;(Sassa).He urged grant recipients never to divulge their social grant details or pin numbers to anybody.&nbsp;"The scammer would claim to be offering a 'R400 Sassa Christmas food hamper' in exchange for supposed 'survey information', which includes asking for the pin numbers to Sassa cards of social grant recipients," said Fritz.&nbsp; The provincial department has no operational control over Sassa.&nbsp;Fritz said they had alerted Sassa to the scam and asked them to investigate.Sassa could not immediately be reached for comment.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.